UIF Commissioner Teboho Maruping says some of the companies will be investigated. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Unemployment Insurance Fund commissioner Teboho Maruping says they are concerned that some companies are applying for relief funds while they are fully functioning during the lockdown. Maruping says that some companies applied for people that have either been dismissed from work, are on maternity leave, or are deceased. READ: COVID-19 fund: UIF shocked at big companies not paying workers The commissioner says some of the companies will be investigated. READ: Employees can now check UIF COVID-19 relief benefit status "We have companies that have applied and during the lockdown, they were actually functioning and have their employees working," Maruping said. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.